observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the financial statements and supporting schedules as of December 31, 2013;


Require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Budget Officer to strictly adhere to the provisions of Section 2.1.1-2.19 of COA Circular No. 2010-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor issue a directive to all Department Heads of the Municipality requiring them to submit their respective Project Procurement Management Plans (PPMPs) to the Secretariat of the Bids and Awards Committee for consolidation into the Annual Procurement Plan (APP).  Otherwise, defer any procurement unless the APP has been prepared and approved.
We also recommended that the Bids and Awards Committee follow strictly the rules and regulations set forth in the 2016 RIRR of RA 9184, specifically the following:
use the 6th Edition of PBDs and incorporate the Specifications, Drawings and Bill of Quantities in the preparation of PBDs to provide prospective bidders all the necessary information that they need to prepare their bids;
invite three observers in all stages of the procurement activities;
conduct pre-bid conference within the prescribed period;
prepare the Checklist of Technical and Financial Component using the prescribed format indicated in the 6th Edition of PBDs and ensure completeness of all required documents, otherwise, declare the participating bidder ineligible;
affix the BAC’s initials in the original copy of Technical Documents, including the Eligibility and Financial Documents as evidence of authentication of submitted bids;
prepare the Abstract of Bids as Read during opening of bids;
require the BAC-TWG to prepare Bid Evaluation Report;
prepare a notice to the bidder with the Lowest Calculated Bid to submit its latest income and business tax returns, and other appropriate licenses and permit required by law;
require the BAC-TWG to prepare the Post-Qualification Report and state clearly in the said report that they have verified and validated all necessary eligibility requirements; and that they have confirmed the LCB’s compliance with the requirements and conditions stated in the Bidding Documents;
submit Performance Securities of the bidders in Table 4 except for Project Nos. 2 and 5;
require the winning bidders to indicate the date of receipt of NOA;
require the winning bidder to submit their DOLE-approved CSHP before approval of the contracts; and
post the NOA and NTP, together with the approved contract, in the PhilGEPS website within three (3) and fifteen (15) calendar days from issuance, respectively.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require all Heads of Departments/Section of the LGU to submit their respective Project Procurement Management Plans (PPMPs) to the Bids and Awards Committee (BAC).
We also recommended that the BAC:
consolidate, through its Secretariat, the PPMPs into the Annual Procurement Plan as basis and guide in all procurement activities;
post the invitation or request for submission of price quotations in the PhilGEPS website for ABC above ₱50,000.00 (Shopping and SVP) except for the mode of procurement not mentioned in Section 54.2 of the 2016 RIRR of RA No. 9184;
prepare BAC Resolution recommending and justifying to the HoPE the use of alternative mode of procurement;
require the suppliers for subsequent procurement to submit the mandatory documentary requirements, i.e. Mayor’s/Business Permit, PhilGEPS Registration Number (except for Negotiated-Emergency Cases), Income/Business Tax Return (For ABCs 500k above) and Omnibus Sworn Statement (For ABCs 500k above) before issuance of Notice of Award, otherwise, the transactions shall be suspended in audit;
prepare BAC Resolution recommending award of contract; and
require the BAC Secretariat, to post in the PhilGEPS website the Notice of Award, Contract or Purchase Order and Notice to Proceed (if any) except for contracts with ABC of Fifty Thousand Pesos (₱50,000.00) and below.
We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant submit justification for processing payments without the acceptance of goods delivered. Henceforth, process payments with duly filled-out and signed Acceptance and Inspection Report.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor:

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit immediately the financial statements and supporting schedules as of December 31, 2013;


Require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Budget Officer to strictly adhere to the provisions of Section 2.1.1-2.19 of COA Circular No. 2010-001.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant be required to:

Transfer the unutilized DRRMF – QRF and MOOE to a Special Trust Fund; 



Maintain separate subsidiary ledgers for the transfer;


Disclose in the Notes to Financial Statements the details of the unexpended balance of LDRRMF using the format in the Annex D of the COA Circular No. 2012-002.

